=============================
ORM (Over Represented Motifs)
=============================
Version 2007.11
Matthieu Defrance <defrance@scmbb.ulb.ac.be>
BiGRe ULB Bruxelles
http://www.lifl.fr/~defrance/ORM


INTRODUCTION
============
  ORM is a command line software that searches for locally 
  overrepresented motifs in a set of DNA sequences.

ARCHIVE CONTENT
===============
  README:    this file
  ormbg.py:  construct background model
  orm.py:    find over-represented oligomer
  ORM.zlib:  library needed by orm.py and ormbg.py
  Example/:  test data files

REQUIREMENTS
============
  Python >= 2.3

INSTALLATION
============
  Unzip the archive

USAGE
=====
  First, construct a statistical background model given sequences found in MM0.fa
  $ ormbg.py -i MM0.fa -m 1 -o MM0.bg  -w 2 --strand=+- --overlap -v 2

  Second, search for overreprented motifs in 1.fa given previouly computed background model
  $ orm.py -b MM0.bg -i 1.fa --heuristic=all --count=hash -v 2 --sort +seq --max rank 3 > outputfile
